  Let's also add Rate Limit Reset: Time remaining (e.g., "Resets in 2h 15m") before my 5-hour message limits reset and Usage Burn Rate: Metrics showing how quickly I am consuming my plan's tokens.

  And then also, can we add a colored Segmented Bar Chart (aka Stacked Bar Chart) that is generated by reading from a json that gets created by a subagent periodically pulling data from the output of /context (run with the auto-wrapper of course).  This might be a bit involved, but let's tackle it.
  Additionally we're going to want to double check that the auto-wrapping for slash-commands is really working, because we've changed all of that, and all of JICM hinges on Jarvis being able to resume work without promting and with no interruptions or idling after context is cleared by /clear from the watcher script.


